{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":920,"text":"So it all came to life"},{"time":2628,"text":"in a dark bar in Madrid."},{"time":5023,"text":"I encountered my colleague\nfrom McGill, Michael Meaney."},{"time":9271,"text":"And we were drinking a few beers,"},{"time":11600,"text":"and like scientists do,"},{"time":13677,"text":"he told me about his work."},{"time":16304,"text":"And he told me that he is interested\nin how mother rats lick their pups"},{"time":23282,"text":"after they were born."},{"time":25656,"text":"And I was sitting there and saying,"},{"time":28099,"text":"\"This is where my tax\ndollars are wasted --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":31123,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":32181,"text":"on this kind of soft science.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":35835,"text":"And he started telling me"},{"time":38356,"text":"that the rats, like humans,"},{"time":41780,"text":"lick their pups in very different ways."},{"time":44250,"text":"Some mothers do a lot of that,"},{"time":47009,"text":"some mothers do very little,"},{"time":49238,"text":"and most are in between."},{"time":51867,"text":"But what's interesting about it"},{"time":53792,"text":"is when he follows these pups\nwhen they become adults --"},{"time":58734,"text":"like, years in human life,\nlong after their mother died."},{"time":62937,"text":"They are completely different animals."},{"time":65029,"text":"The animals that were licked\nand groomed heavily,"},{"time":69426,"text":"the high-licking and grooming,"},{"time":72059,"text":"are not stressed."},{"time":74022,"text":"They have different sexual behavior."},{"time":76295,"text":"They have a different way of living"},{"time":79274,"text":"than those that were not treated\nas intensively by their mothers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85934,"text":"So then I was thinking to myself:"},{"time":89122,"text":"Is this magic?"},{"time":91002,"text":"How does this work?"},{"time":92395,"text":"As geneticists would like you to think,"},{"time":95390,"text":"perhaps the mother had\nthe \"bad mother\" gene"},{"time":99386,"text":"that caused her pups to be stressful,"},{"time":103047,"text":"and then it was passed\nfrom generation to generation;"},{"time":105618,"text":"it's all determined by genetics."},{"time":108342,"text":"Or is it possible that something\nelse is going on here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":111860,"text":"In rats, we can ask\nthis question and answer it."},{"time":115455,"text":"So what we did is\na cross-fostering experiment."},{"time":119084,"text":"You essentially separate the litter,\nthe babies of this rat, at birth,"},{"time":123863,"text":"to two kinds of fostering mothers --"},{"time":125754,"text":"not the real mothers,\nbut mothers that will take care of them:"},{"time":129106,"text":"high-licking mothers\nand low-licking mothers."},{"time":131384,"text":"And you can do the opposite\nwith the low-licking pups."},{"time":135708,"text":"And the remarkable answer was,"},{"time":138105,"text":"it wasn't important\nwhat gene you got from your mother."},{"time":142168,"text":"It was not the biological mother\nthat defined this property of these rats."},{"time":147940,"text":"It is the mother that\ntook care of the pups."},{"time":152771,"text":"So how can this work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156921,"text":"I am an a epigeneticist."},{"time":158748,"text":"I am interested in how genes are marked"},{"time":162444,"text":"by a chemical mark"},{"time":164184,"text":"during embryogenesis, during the time\nwe're in the womb of our mothers,"},{"time":169013,"text":"and decide which gene will be expressed"},{"time":171516,"text":"in what tissue."},{"time":172722,"text":"Different genes are expressed in the brain\nthan in the liver and the eye."},{"time":177718,"text":"And we thought: Is it possible"},{"time":180581,"text":"that the mother is somehow\nreprogramming the gene of her offspring"},{"time":187552,"text":"through her behavior?"},{"time":189125,"text":"And we spent 10 years,"},{"time":190760,"text":"and we found that there is a cascade\nof biochemical events"},{"time":194825,"text":"by which the licking and grooming\nof the mother, the care of the mother,"},{"time":198292,"text":"is translated to biochemical signals"},{"time":200799,"text":"that go into the nucleus and into the DNA"},{"time":204134,"text":"and program it differently."},{"time":206236,"text":"So now the animal can prepare\nitself for life:"},{"time":211156,"text":"Is life going to be harsh?"},{"time":213801,"text":"Is there going to be a lot of food?"},{"time":215587,"text":"Are there going to be a lot of cats\nand snakes around,"},{"time":218136,"text":"or will I live\nin an upper-class neighborhood"},{"time":220483,"text":"where all I have to do\nis behave well and proper,"},{"time":223214,"text":"and that will gain me social acceptance?"},{"time":226978,"text":"And now one can think about\nhow important that process can be"},{"time":232593,"text":"for our lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233792,"text":"We inherit our DNA from our ancestors."},{"time":237411,"text":"The DNA is old."},{"time":239364,"text":"It evolved during evolution."},{"time":241938,"text":"But it doesn't tell us\nif you are going to be born in Stockholm,"},{"time":246295,"text":"where the days are long in the summer\nand short in the winter,"},{"time":249705,"text":"or in Ecuador,"},{"time":251034,"text":"where there's an equal number of hours\nfor day and night all year round."},{"time":254591,"text":"And that has such an enormous [effect]\non our physiology."},{"time":259489,"text":"So what we suggest is,\nperhaps what happens early in life,"},{"time":263749,"text":"those signals that come\nthrough the mother,"},{"time":265940,"text":"tell the child what kind of social world\nyou're going to be living in."},{"time":270479,"text":"It will be harsh, and you'd better\nbe anxious and be stressful,"},{"time":273903,"text":"or it's going to be an easy world,\nand you have to be different."},{"time":277050,"text":"Is it going to be a world\nwith a lot of light or little light?"},{"time":280264,"text":"Is it going to be a world\nwith a lot of food or little food?"},{"time":284273,"text":"If there's no food around,"},{"time":285821,"text":"you'd better develop your brain to binge\nwhenever you see a meal,"},{"time":290461,"text":"or store every piece of food\nthat you have as fat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296819,"text":"So this is good."},{"time":298273,"text":"Evolution has selected this"},{"time":300154,"text":"to allow our fixed, old DNA\nto function in a dynamic way"},{"time":305074,"text":"in new environments."},{"time":307377,"text":"But sometimes things can go wrong;"},{"time":310706,"text":"for example, if you're born\nto a poor family"},{"time":314592,"text":"and the signals are, \"You better binge,"},{"time":317545,"text":"you better eat every piece of food\nyou're going to encounter.\""},{"time":320784,"text":"But now we humans\nand our brain have evolved,"},{"time":323060,"text":"have changed evolution even faster."},{"time":325180,"text":"Now you can buy McDonald's for one dollar."},{"time":328568,"text":"And therefore, the preparation\nthat we had by our mothers"},{"time":335002,"text":"is turning out to be maladaptive."},{"time":338351,"text":"The same preparation that was supposed\nto protect us from hunger and famine"},{"time":342588,"text":"is going to cause obesity,"},{"time":345069,"text":"cardiovascular problems\nand metabolic disease."},{"time":348666,"text":"So this concept that genes\ncould be marked by our experience,"},{"time":352162,"text":"and especially the early life experience,"},{"time":354487,"text":"can provide us a unifying explanation"},{"time":357325,"text":"of both health and disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360612,"text":"But is true only for rats?"},{"time":362994,"text":"The problem is, we cannot\ntest this in humans,"},{"time":365970,"text":"because ethically, we cannot administer\nchild adversity in a random way."},{"time":370106,"text":"So if a poor child develops\na certain property,"},{"time":373434,"text":"we don't know whether\nthis is caused by poverty"},{"time":377197,"text":"or whether poor people have bad genes."},{"time":380045,"text":"So geneticists will try to tell you\nthat poor people are poor"},{"time":383184,"text":"because their genes make them poor."},{"time":385264,"text":"Epigeneticists will tell you"},{"time":387248,"text":"poor people are in a bad environment\nor an impoverished environment"},{"time":391382,"text":"that creates that phenotype,\nthat property."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395576,"text":"So we moved to look\ninto our cousins, the monkeys."},{"time":402087,"text":"My colleague, Stephen Suomi,\nhas been rearing monkeys"},{"time":405805,"text":"in two different ways:"},{"time":406990,"text":"randomly separated the monkey\nfrom the mother"},{"time":409915,"text":"and reared her with a nurse"},{"time":412531,"text":"and surrogate motherhood conditions."},{"time":415514,"text":"So these monkeys didn't have\na mother; they had a nurse."},{"time":418209,"text":"And other monkeys were reared\nwith their normal, natural mothers."},{"time":422853,"text":"And when they were old,\nthey were completely different animals."},{"time":427573,"text":"The monkeys that had a mother\ndid not care about alcohol,"},{"time":430690,"text":"they were not sexually aggressive."},{"time":432393,"text":"The monkeys that didn't have a mother\nwere aggressive, were stressed"},{"time":436184,"text":"and were alcoholics."},{"time":438482,"text":"So we looked at their DNA\nearly after birth, to see:"},{"time":443988,"text":"Is it possible that the mother is marking?"},{"time":446779,"text":"Is there a signature of the mother\nin the DNA of the offspring?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":452161,"text":"These are Day-14 monkeys,"},{"time":454437,"text":"and what you see here is the modern way\nby which we study epigenetics."},{"time":458537,"text":"We can now map those chemical marks,\nwhich we call methylation marks,"},{"time":463224,"text":"on DNA at a single nucleotide resolution."},{"time":466506,"text":"We can map the entire genome."},{"time":468407,"text":"We can now compare the monkey\nthat had a mother or not."},{"time":471498,"text":"And here's a visual presentation of this."},{"time":473476,"text":"What you see is the genes\nthat got more methylated are red."},{"time":478237,"text":"The genes that got\nless methylated are green."},{"time":481275,"text":"You can see many genes are changing,"},{"time":483783,"text":"because not having a mother\nis not just one thing --"},{"time":486521,"text":"it affects the whole way;"},{"time":488076,"text":"it sends signals about the whole way\nyour world is going to look"},{"time":491608,"text":"when you become an adult."},{"time":493391,"text":"And you can see the two groups of monkeys"},{"time":495836,"text":"extremely well-separated from each other."},{"time":499392,"text":"How early does this develop?"},{"time":502078,"text":"These monkeys already\ndidn't see their mothers,"},{"time":504315,"text":"so they had a social experience."},{"time":506038,"text":"Do we sense our social status,\neven at the moment of birth?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":511131,"text":"So in this experiment,\nwe took placentas of monkeys"},{"time":515204,"text":"that had different social status."},{"time":517698,"text":"What's interesting about social rank\nis that across all living beings,"},{"time":523096,"text":"they will structure\nthemselves by hierarchy."},{"time":526345,"text":"Monkey number one is the boss;"},{"time":528557,"text":"monkey number four is the peon."},{"time":530919,"text":"You put four monkeys in a cage,"},{"time":533382,"text":"there will always be a boss\nand always be a peon."},{"time":537448,"text":"And what's interesting\nis that the monkey number one"},{"time":541320,"text":"is much healthier than monkey number four."},{"time":544776,"text":"And if you put them in a cage,"},{"time":546604,"text":"monkey number one will not eat as much."},{"time":551325,"text":"Monkey number four will eat [a lot]."},{"time":554129,"text":"And what you see here\nin this methylation mapping,"},{"time":558426,"text":"a dramatic separation at birth"},{"time":561225,"text":"of the animals that had\na high social status"},{"time":563963,"text":"versus the animals\nthat did not have a high status."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567349,"text":"So we are born already knowing\nthe social information,"},{"time":571604,"text":"and that social information\nis not bad or good,"},{"time":574681,"text":"it just prepares us for life,"},{"time":576124,"text":"because we have to program\nour biology differently"},{"time":580389,"text":"if we are in the high\nor the low social status."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584326,"text":"But how can you study this in humans?"},{"time":586710,"text":"We can't do experiments,\nwe can't administer adversity to humans."},{"time":590182,"text":"But God does experiments with humans,"},{"time":592799,"text":"and it's called natural disasters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595111,"text":"One of the hardest natural disasters\nin Canadian history"},{"time":599395,"text":"happened in my province of Quebec."},{"time":601829,"text":"It's the ice storm of 1998."},{"time":604256,"text":"We lost our entire electrical grid\nbecause of an ice storm"},{"time":608080,"text":"when the temperatures\nwere, in the dead of winter in Quebec,"},{"time":611101,"text":"minus 20 to minus 30."},{"time":613074,"text":"And there were pregnant\nmothers during that time."},{"time":616082,"text":"And my colleague Suzanne King\nfollowed the children of these mothers"},{"time":622138,"text":"for 15 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624565,"text":"And what happened was,\nthat as the stress increased --"},{"time":628835,"text":"and here we had objective\nmeasures of stress:"},{"time":631467,"text":"How long were you without power?\nWhere did you spend your time?"},{"time":635929,"text":"Was it in your mother-in-law's apartment\nor in some posh country home?"},{"time":640956,"text":"So all of these added up\nto a social stress scale,"},{"time":643638,"text":"and you can ask the question:"},{"time":645044,"text":"How did the children look?"},{"time":648112,"text":"And it appears that as stress increases,"},{"time":650770,"text":"the children develop more autism,"},{"time":652852,"text":"they develop more metabolic diseases"},{"time":655415,"text":"and they develop more autoimmune diseases."},{"time":658787,"text":"We would map the methylation state,"},{"time":661235,"text":"and again, you see the green genes\nbecoming red as stress increases,"},{"time":666797,"text":"the red genes becoming green\nas stress increases,"},{"time":670313,"text":"an entire rearrangement\nof the genome in response to stress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677442,"text":"So if we can program genes,"},{"time":680675,"text":"if we are not just the slaves\nof the history of our genes,"},{"time":684672,"text":"that they could be programmed,\ncan we deprogram them?"},{"time":688093,"text":"Because epigenetic causes\ncan cause diseases like cancer,"},{"time":693659,"text":"metabolic disease"},{"time":695486,"text":"and mental health diseases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698120,"text":"Let's talk about cocaine addiction."},{"time":701575,"text":"Cocaine addiction is a terrible situation"},{"time":704655,"text":"that can lead to death\nand to loss of human life."},{"time":709545,"text":"We asked the question:"},{"time":711494,"text":"Can we reprogram the addicted brain"},{"time":714757,"text":"to make that animal not addicted anymore?"},{"time":720377,"text":"We used a cocaine addiction model"},{"time":724681,"text":"that recapitulates what happens in humans."},{"time":726794,"text":"In humans, you're in high school,"},{"time":729486,"text":"some friends suggest you use some cocaine,"},{"time":731590,"text":"you take cocaine, nothing happens."},{"time":733420,"text":"Months pass by, something reminds you\nof what happened the first time,"},{"time":737645,"text":"a pusher pushes cocaine,"},{"time":739309,"text":"and you become addicted\nand your life has changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742165,"text":"In rats, we do the same thing."},{"time":743835,"text":"My colleague, Gal Yadid,"},{"time":745434,"text":"he trains the animals\nto get used to cocaine,"},{"time":748458,"text":"then for one month, no cocaine."},{"time":751610,"text":"Then he reminds them of the party\nwhen they saw the cocaine the first time"},{"time":755310,"text":"by cue, the colors of the cage\nwhen they saw cocaine."},{"time":758150,"text":"And they go crazy."},{"time":759826,"text":"They will press the lever to get cocaine"},{"time":762297,"text":"until they die."},{"time":764047,"text":"We first determined that the difference\nbetween these animals"},{"time":768514,"text":"is that during that time\nwhen nothing happens,"},{"time":771239,"text":"there's no cocaine around,"},{"time":773035,"text":"their epigenome is rearranged."},{"time":774980,"text":"Their genes are re-marked\nin a different way,"},{"time":777893,"text":"and when the cue comes,\ntheir genome is ready"},{"time":781659,"text":"to develop this addictive phenotype."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784565,"text":"So we treated these animals with drugs\nthat either increase DNA methylation,"},{"time":791359,"text":"which was the epigenetic\nmarker to look at,"},{"time":793607,"text":"or decrease epigenetic markings."},{"time":797114,"text":"And we found that\nif we increased methylation,"},{"time":800393,"text":"these animals go even crazier."},{"time":802300,"text":"They become more craving for cocaine."},{"time":804808,"text":"But if we reduce the DNA methylation,"},{"time":808258,"text":"the animals are not addicted anymore."},{"time":810386,"text":"We have reprogrammed them."},{"time":812029,"text":"And a fundamental difference\nbetween an epigenetic drug"},{"time":815359,"text":"and any other drug"},{"time":816689,"text":"is that with epigenetic drugs,"},{"time":818885,"text":"we essentially remove\nthe signs of experience,"},{"time":823041,"text":"and once they're gone,"},{"time":825192,"text":"they will not come back\nunless you have the same experience."},{"time":828237,"text":"The animal now is reprogrammed."},{"time":829915,"text":"So when we visited the animals\n30 days, 60 days later,"},{"time":834160,"text":"which is in human terms\nmany years of life,"},{"time":837103,"text":"they were still not addicted --\nby a single epigenetic treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844472,"text":"So what did we learn about DNA?"},{"time":847767,"text":"DNA is not just a sequence of letters;"},{"time":850916,"text":"it's not just a script."},{"time":853059,"text":"DNA is a dynamic movie."},{"time":856367,"text":"Our experiences are being written\ninto this movie, which is interactive."},{"time":861302,"text":"You're, like, watching a movie\nof your life, with the DNA,"},{"time":864879,"text":"with your remote control."},{"time":866685,"text":"You can remove an actor and add an actor."},{"time":870872,"text":"And so you have, in spite\nof the deterministic nature of genetics,"},{"time":876791,"text":"you have control of the way\nyour genes look,"},{"time":880504,"text":"and this has a tremendous\noptimistic message"},{"time":883798,"text":"for the ability to now encounter\nsome of the deadly diseases"},{"time":887330,"text":"like cancer, mental health,"},{"time":890258,"text":"with a new approach,"},{"time":893210,"text":"looking at them as maladaptation."},{"time":895768,"text":"And if we can epigenetically intervene,"},{"time":898866,"text":"[we can] reverse the movie\nby removing an actor"},{"time":902386,"text":"and setting up a new narrative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906028,"text":"So what I told you today is,"},{"time":908549,"text":"our DNA is really combined\nof two components,"},{"time":913665,"text":"two layers of information."},{"time":916106,"text":"One layer of information is old,"},{"time":919805,"text":"evolved from millions\nof years of evolution."},{"time":923334,"text":"It is fixed and very hard to change."},{"time":927411,"text":"The other layer of information\nis the epigenetic layer,"},{"time":931285,"text":"which is open and dynamic"},{"time":935204,"text":"and sets up a narrative\nthat is interactive,"},{"time":939820,"text":"that allows us to control,\nto a large extent, our destiny,"},{"time":947695,"text":"to help the destiny of our children"},{"time":951175,"text":"and to hopefully conquer disease"},{"time":955354,"text":"and serious health challenges"},{"time":959794,"text":"that have plagued humankind\nfor a long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":963429,"text":"So even though we are determined"},{"time":966846,"text":"by our genes,"},{"time":968625,"text":"we have a degree of freedom"},{"time":971716,"text":"that can set up our life\nto a life of responsibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975873,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977117,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}